Don't let fireworks be a burden, see firsthand.

A face perspiring has the value which it has never had, a face perspiring, no doubt, for the first time, and for the first time which is made visible by a handholding mirror.

Japanese identity, broadly speaking, is a whole series of local identities, firmly in place, the people, the culture, the religions, the history. All hand held in place very securely.

Only if you know your face clearly will you know what you are like. Take a good long look at yourself. I tell you, whatever your appearance, however notoriously bad it is considered, it emanates, it carries within its reflection the past of the world.

This rule is very easy to understand, open the page at Experience and draw a good long look at your face. What kind of face do you have there? What type of face am I talking about? We are more or less obvious about a thing that has to do with externals. Also nature puts in trails and clues all around us for us to follow easily.

Handsome, ugly, we have them all. We are all one and all are faces, and all are natural. Preconceived notions about bodily type are of no use whatsoever.

Oddly enough, though the hand seems to move, ab it cannot make for itself any sense of touch. Any organ which, especially in a cultural aspect of sense, must simply be eliminated
